description: These sweet-and-spicy butternut squash fries are packed with flavor from yummy sriracha. Oven baked, and made with just three simple ingredients, they're so much healthier than traditional fries!
keywords: Baked Sriracha Butternut Squash Fries, Butternut Squash Fries, vegetable fries
name: Baked Sriracha Butternut Squash Fries
recipeIngredient: 1 tbsp peanut (vegetable, canola or any other neutral-flavored oil)
1 large butternut squash (peeled, seeded and cut into evenly-sized steak fries)

recipeInstructions.text: Whisk together oil and sriracha in a large bowl. Transfer butternut squash fries to bowl and toss to coat. (It’s messy, but use your hands—it works best!) Pour fries onto a rimmed baking sheet and arrange in a single layer. Sprinkle with salt.
Bake for 20 minutes, then carefully flip fries over using tongs or a spatula. Sprinkle with additional salt and bake for 20 minutes more or until tender and browned on edges.
